.TH "drbd_header_size" 9 "drbd_header_size" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drbd_header_size \- size of a packet header
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" drbd_header_size
.BI "(struct drbd_connection *connection "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "connection" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

The header size is a multiple of 8, so any payload following the header is
word aligned on 64-bit architectures.  (The bitmap send and receive code
relies on this.)
